                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <hr class="small">
                    <p class="lead">A simple phone charger is used to provide power to the microcontroller. 
                    Since the microcontroller runs on 3.3V and the relay requires a 5V source, VIN on the micro is used, since VIN is the raw power before being regulated down to 3.3V.
                    </p>
                    <hr class="small">
                    <p class="lead">The wires used are rated for 16A, but the relay is only rated for 10A. A 10A fuse is installed in case of overloading.</p>
                    <hr class="small">
                    <p class="lead">The relay board is active low, so pull down resistors are placed so that the outlets are default on while the microcontroller is in an indeterminent state.</p>
                </div>
